			abstractLg2:
				'The purpose of the survey of government employees is to collect information on the employees of the State Civil Service not available in administrative data in order to allow a more detailed analysis of the determinants of the salary and to deepen important topics related to wages, such as differences in remuneration between men and women.\nThis survey complements the Ecmoss device (labor cost and structure of earnings survey), which allows INSEE to produce the European structural statistics requested by Eurostat and Dares to ensure annual monitoring of the structure of earnings and working time.',
