				'The SINE programme (New Enterprises Information System) serves to analyse the profile of the creator and the start-up and development conditions of new enterprises and the problems young enterprises encounter over the first five years of their existence and the effects on employment of business start-ups.\n\nIt meets the demand of different bodies responsible for developing new enterprise support policies : Chambers of Commerce and Industry, Chambers of Trade, banks, regional councils, Directorate General for Competitiveness, Industry and Services (DGCIS), Business Start-up Agency (APCE), support for the innovation and growth of small and medium enterprises (OSEO), France Initiative Réseau, Association for the right to economic initiative (ADIE), etc.\n\nSince the first survey of the 2010 set featured specific surveying of auto-entrepreneurs has been adopted, though nonetheless tackling the same topics as the surveying of other creators.',
